[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mortonhall Crematorium fire causes major damage

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire at the Mortonhall Crematorium in Edinburgh has badly damaged one of its buildings, firefighters have confirmed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
At least 35 firefighters tackled the blaze which broke out in a roof just before 19:00 on Tuesday.
There was nobody in the building at the time. Crews worked through the night to bring the fire under control and to assess the damage.
Edinburgh city council said funerals have been postponed for the rest of the week.
